description:
&lt;p&gt;An exciting opportunity for a Clinical Specialist Assessor has arisen at University Hospitals of Morecambe Bay NHS Trust within a new Frailty pathway within Community Services.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post will closely align to our existing Community Health Services such as Rapid Response in the management and coordination of this patient group.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Frailty Coordination Service will enable easy access to decision making support to enable management of patients within the Community with support from a range of services to support admission avoidance or where appropriate refer for an admission.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post holder would work closely with Primary/ Secondary Care, Adult Social Care and Voluntary agencies in the management of this patient group.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The service will:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Create a clear and simple route for Primary Care (and other referrers) to access the most appropriate care for their patient that avoids a default route to hospital&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Align existing services/teams to deliver equity of service across the health and social care economy&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support the care for Frail Elderly people in an environment that meets with their needs and their wishes&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Aim to improve the quality outcomes for patients&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Encourage and improve the understanding of frailty across the system&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Optimise patient flow, utilising digital platforms where possible&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;NameAlison SuartJob titleClinical Service ManagerEmail addressalison.suart@mbht.nhs.ukTelephone number07825103431&lt;/p&gt;
